  {
    "id": "intel--f3d1d129a889715f",
    "stix_id": "indicator--f3d1d129a889715fb211f74739db91fa",
    "title": "Angular Expressions - Remote Code Execution using filters",
    "description": "## Impact\n\nAn attacker can write a malicious expression that escapes the sandbox to execute arbitrary code on the system.\n\nExample of vulnerable code:\n\n```\nconst expressions = require(\"angular-expressions\");\nconst result = expressions.compile(\"a | __proto__\")({}, {});\n```\n\nThis should throw the error : Filter '__proto__' is not defined, however, this shows : \n\nUncaught SyntaxError: Unexpected identifier 'Object'\n\nWith a more complex (undisclosed) payload, one can get full access to Arbitrary code execution on the system.\n\n## Vulnerable versions : \n\nangular-expressions <= 1.5.1\n\n## Patches\n\nThe problem has been patched in version 1.5.2 of angular-expressions.\n\n## Credits\n\nCredits go to San Gil from [www.securityoffice.io](https://securityoffice.io/) who has found the issue and reported it t",
    "source_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-pw8r-6689-xvf4",
    "feed_source": "github_advisory",
    "published_at": "2026-05-11T16:20:58Z",
    "processed_at": "2026-05-11T16:41:22Z",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-11T16:20:58Z",
    "severity": "CRITICAL",
    "risk_score": 5.0,
    "threat_type": "OSS-ADVISORY",
    "tags": [
      "github",
      "advisory",
      "critical",
      "oss"
    ],
    "cves": [
      "CVE-2026-44643"
    ],
    "iocs": [],
    "ioc_count": 0,
    "tlp": "TLP:CLEAR",
    "actor_tag": "UNC-CDB-INGEST",
    "apex_ai_summary": "[CRITICAL] OSS-ADVISORY advisory. Risk score 5.0/10. Full APEX AI analysis available to Pro subscribers.",
    "apex_ai_score": 5.0,
    "status": "active",
    "schema_version": "stable-v1.0-apex"
  },
