    "description": "A widely used Go library called fsnotify has found itself at the center of a supply chain security scare after a sudden change in maintainer access triggered alarm across the open source community.  The project provides cross-platform filesystem notifications for applications running on Windows, Linux, macOS, BSD, and illumos. Contributors were removed from its GitHub [&#8230;] \n The post  Popular Go Library fsnotify Raises Supply Chain Alarms After Maintainer Access Changes  appeared first on",
