    "description": "Cybercriminals are getting creative with how they lure victims into downloading malware, and a new campaign involving a fake version of Anthropic&#8217;s Claude AI assistant is raising serious concerns. Attackers set up a convincing lookalike website to distribute a dangerous installer that quietly plants a backdoor on infected systems. The campaign uses a chain of [&#8230;] \n The post  Hackers Use PlugX-Like DLL Sideloading Chain in Fake Claude Malware Campaign  appeared first on  Cyber Securit",
