  },
  {
    "id": "intel--90b499e17547b70a",
    "stix_id": "indicator--90b499e17547b70aeb81db913961739d",
    "title": "Ella Core has handover failures during concurrent Security Mode Command",
    "description": "## Summary\n\nElla Core didn't enforce security rules on concurrent running of security procedures defined in TS 33.501 §6.9.5.1 — it could send a NAS Security Mode Command while an N2 handover was still pending (and vice versa).\n\n## Impact\n\nConcurrent Security Mode Command and N2 handover produce a KgNB mismatch between the UE and target gNB, causing the handover to fail. Requires a stalled gNB + re-registration race to trigger.\n\n## Fix\n\nElla Core now enforces both rules from §6.9.5.1, blocking concurrent Security Mode Command and N2 handover procedures.",
    "source_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-mc29-hmx6-856q",
    "feed_source": "github_advisory",
    "published_at": "2026-05-11T15:29:41Z",
    "processed_at": "2026-05-11T16:41:22Z",
