    "description": "Hackers are once again targeting developers and AI enthusiasts by impersonating popular open-source tools on GitHub. This time, the target is DeepSeek TUI, a legitimate terminal-based intelligent agent that allows users to interact with DeepSeek large language models directly from the command line. With the recent release of DeepSeek v4 and a widely shared post [&#8230;] \n The post  Hackers Use Fake DeepSeek TUI GitHub Repositories to Deliver Malware  appeared first on  Cyber Security News .",
