  {
    "id": "intel--46fff968efcc75d7",
    "stix_id": "indicator--46fff968efcc75d7af180192a37a8480",
    "title": "urllib3: Sensitive headers forwarded across origins in proxied low-level redirects",
    "description": "### Impact\n\nWhen following cross-origin redirects for requests made using urllib3’s high-level APIs, such as `urllib3.request()`, `PoolManager.request()`, and `ProxyManager.request()`, sensitive headers — `Authorization`, `Cookie`, and `Proxy-Authorization` (defined in `Retry.DEFAULT_REMOVE_HEADERS_ON_REDIRECT`) — are stripped by default, as expected.\n\nHowever, cross-origin redirects followed from the low-level API via `ProxyManager.connection_from_url().urlopen(..., assert_same_host=False)` still forward these sensitive headers.\n\n### Affected usage\n\nApplications and libraries using urllib3 versions earlier than 2.7.0 may be affected if they allow cross-origin redirects while making requests through `HTTPConnection.urlopen()` instances created via `ProxyManager.connection_from_url()`.\n\n###",
    "source_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-qccp-gfcp-xxvc",
    "feed_source": "github_advisory",
    "published_at": "2026-05-11T14:51:20Z",
    "processed_at": "2026-05-11T16:41:22Z",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-11T14:51:20Z",
    "severity": "HIGH",
    "risk_score": 5.0,
    "threat_type": "OSS-ADVISORY",
    "tags": [
      "github",
      "advisory",
      "high",
      "oss"
    ],
