    "actor_tag": "UNC-CDB-INGEST",
    "apex_ai_summary": "[HIGH] OSS-ADVISORY advisory. Risk score 8.8/10. Full APEX AI analysis available to Pro subscribers.",
    "apex_ai_score": 8.8,
    "status": "active",
    "schema_version": "stable-v1.0-apex"
  },
  {
    "id": "intel--7eb92ba117174fde",
    "stix_id": "indicator--7eb92ba117174fded81709da75f55208",
    "title": "Open WebUI has inconsistent authorization controls within memories API",
    "description": "### Summary\n\nAuthorization controls surrounding the memories API were inconsistent, resulting in the ability of a standard user to delete, restore, and view the contents of other users' memories.\n\n\n### Details\n\nUsing a newly created non-admin user with no existing memories, it is possible to view existing memories via `POST /api/v1/memories/query`. See below under the PoC section, where a call to `GET /api/v1/memories/` returns `[]` (as expected) but a call to `POST /api/v1/memories/query` reveals memories created by other users.\n\nSimilarly, even if a non-admin user cannot modify another user's memory data via `POST /api/v1/memories/{memory_id}/update`, the endpoint's response improperly leaks the content of that memory if a valid memory_id is known.\n\nThe `DELETE /api/v1/memories/{memory_i",
    "source_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-hmjq-crxp-7rjw",
    "feed_source": "github_advisory",
    "published_at": "2026-05-11T14:25:49Z",
    "processed_at": "2026-05-11T16:41:22Z",
    "timestamp": "2026-05-11T14:25:49Z",
    "severity": "HIGH",
    "risk_score": 8.3,
    "threat_type": "OSS-ADVISORY",
    "tags": [
      "github",
      "advisory",
      "high",
      "oss"
    ],
    "cves": [
