  {
    "id": "intel--dcd58fa12c3c3cc5",
    "stix_id": "indicator--dcd58fa12c3c3cc5aa567cbcec9c9356",
    "title": "PraisonAI knowledge-store backends interpolate unvalidated collection names into SQL and CQL queries",
    "description": "### Summary\nPraisonAI exposes optional SQL/CQL-backed knowledge-store implementations that build table and index identifiers from unvalidated `name` and `collection` arguments. Applications that pass untrusted collection names into these backends can trigger SQL or CQL injection.\n\n### Details\nThis issue affects the public persistence layer exported by [persistence/__init__.py](/Users/shmulc/Stuff/tmp/first-cve/scans/variant-hunt/PraisonAI/src/praisonai/praisonai/persistence/__init__.py:1), which exposes `KnowledgeStore` and `create_knowledge_store()`. The factory wires the affected backends as supported knowledge-store providers in [[persistence/factory.py](https://github.com/Users/shmulc/Stuff/tmp/first-cve/scans/variant-hunt/PraisonAI/src/praisonai/praisonai/persistence/factory.py:112)](",
    "source_url": "https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-3643-7v76-5cj2",
    "feed_source": "github_advisory",
    "published_at": "2026-05-11T13:57:18Z",
